    "costs": null,
    "actions_taken": [],
    "summary": "Derrick barge William Kallop, after completing installation of Arena Offshore's South Timbalier 131 K platform and recovering anchors, lost control when tugboat Offshore King could not maintain position in strong current. The barge drifted into adjacent Chevron platform complex ST 130D, damaging the riser guard, 12-inch beam below cellar deck, stairway, landing, and main deck beams. The E-W and N-S edge beams deflected inward 12 inches, and the vertical diagonal bracing the E-W beam required replacement.",
